In this article, President Trump addresses the issue of sanctuary jurisdictions and their impact on immigration enforcement. He criticizes cities such as San Francisco, California, and New York for refusing to cooperate with Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) by not turning over criminal aliens. Trump argues that these jurisdictions are endangering American citizens by releasing criminals into communities and obstructing immigration enforcement. He calls on Congress to block funds for jurisdictions that shield dangerous criminals and emphasizes the need to prioritize the safety of American lives and cities.